Ed - Are we still defending our awards? Damn! Gary, you seem to be off base here. Do you want to clarify your objection to Ed? Exactly what is it that you found objectionable to which you felt like taking a slam at him?<br><br>
Tom - This is what I wrote:<br>
&quot;Some vets hate the awards they got. Some think they represent who they are. Some think not a twit about their medals gathering dust in their closet. Some folks get offended when you mention what you were awarded. Some get bored. And some get excited.&quot;<br><br>
The one piece that you took out of context and quoted inaccurately was, &quot;Some think they(medals) represent who they are. Let me explain that small part for you. There are vets who believe that their sole existance in life are what they did when they earned their medals. Consequently, they spend the rest of their lives trying to live or rather, relive, those days over and over again, in the vain attempt to give credence to their existance. Does this apply to Ed? I have no idea, because I have never met the man nor have I had engaged him other than this forum. But from what I do know, I think not.<br><br>
But, if you read what Gary had written, the fact that he took offense with Ed does justify part of my paragraph, &quot;Some folks get offended when you mention what you were awarded.&quot; Seems rather sad. All the rest of you post I agree with.
